Sentencas: The microstructure of a fuel-electrode has a significant influence on the whole performance of fuel electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) fabricated by aqueous-based tape casting.
Titulo: Influence of pore former on electrochemical performance of fuel-electrode supported SOFCs manufactured by aqueous-based tape-casting

Sentencas: While in the aqueous-based tape casting process, the fuel electrode porosity, which plays a key role in the final fuel electrode microstructure, mainly comes from the pore former (potato starch in this case).
Titulo: Influence of pore former on electrochemical performance of fuel-electrode supported SOFCs manufactured by aqueous-based tape-casting

Sentencas: Different contents of starch are added into fuel electrode slurries.
Titulo: Influence of pore former on electrochemical performance of fuel-electrode supported SOFCs manufactured by aqueous-based tape-casting

Sentencas: When the starch content is 2.5%wt, the cells show the best performance.
Titulo: Influence of pore former on electrochemical performance of fuel-electrode supported SOFCs manufactured by aqueous-based tape-casting

Sentencas: After one thermal cycle and discharging at a constant voltage of 0.7 V and temperature of 800 degrees C, the peak power density has reached similar to 1263 mW cm(-2) with humidified H-2 as the fuel and air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Influence of pore former on electrochemical performance of fuel-electrode supported SOFCs manufactured by aqueous-based tape-casting
